,"test_description":"Create a temp git repo, commit baseline, add/modify a real binary file, run the CLI via subprocess, and assert process exits successfully and binary file appears in counts/report. MATRIX-USAGE: Integration vs System row settled this (real subprocess/binary diff behavior required).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.11,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: unborn-HEAD behavior is a real git repository state with specific subprocess exit/output semantics; this is not faithfully represented by a mock without duplicating git behavior. MOCK-HIDE: mocked git responses can miss the exact error path. Rejection-gate: I considered Integration, but the behavior text explicitly depends on repo state ('no commits yet') that is enforced by real git semantics. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by absence of AI/ML calls.","test_description":"Initialize a new repo with no commits, execute CLI as a subprocess, assert zero/empty structured report and no uncaught error. MATRIX-USAGE: Integration vs System row settled this (real git process state is the failure boundary).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The counts in the report match the actual change history of the repository being analyzed.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: correctness is defined against actual git history semantics, so minimum trustworthy test infra is a real repository with real commits and CLI subprocess execution. MOCK-HIDE: replacing git/history with fixtures risks validating against an incorrect model of history. Rejection-gate: I considered Integration, but behavior text anchors truth to 'actual change history of the repository', which disqualifies purely in-process substitutes as the minimum. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified (no model output dependency).","test_description":"Build a temp repo with a scripted commit history including add/delete/rename/modify events, run CLI, and compare emitted counts to counts derived independently from git commands over that same repo. MATRIX-USAGE: Integration vs System row settled this (real git history semantics required).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The output is identical whether the changes being analyzed are staged or unstaged.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: staged vs unstaged is a git index/working-tree state distinction that depends on real repository mechanics and subprocess behavior. MOCK-HIDE: stubs can easily miss subtle index/worktree divergences and always pass. Rejection-gate: I considered Integration, but behavior text explicitly compares two real git states ('staged or unstaged'), which requires real git state transitions. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by no AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"In a temp repo, produce equivalent change sets once as unstaged and once staged, run CLI in each state, normalize deterministic fields, and assert identical structured output. MATRIX-USAGE: Integration vs System row settled this (real git index/worktree behavior required).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.92,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
